# Day 9 - Linux Command Reference Guide

> A complete reference of Linux commands learned during the first nine days of my Linux learning journey.

---

# System Information & Package Management

## echo

Displays text on the terminal.

```bash
echo "Hello World"
```

---

## id

Displays information about the current user.

```bash
id
```

Example Output

```
uid=1000(user) gid=1000(user)
```

---

## id -un

Displays only the username.

```bash
id -un
```

---

## whoami

Shows the currently logged-in user.

```bash
whoami
```

---

## sudo

Runs a command with administrator (root) privileges.

```bash
sudo command
```

---

## apt

Ubuntu package manager.

Examples

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt full-upgrade
sudo apt autoremove
apt list --upgradable
```

---

## sudo reboot

Restarts the computer.

```bash
sudo reboot
```

---

## df -h

Displays disk usage in human-readable format.

```bash
df -h
```

---

## git --version

Checks installed Git version.

```bash
git --version
```

---

## code .

Opens the current directory in Visual Studio Code.

```bash
code .
```

---

# Navigation Commands

## pwd

Prints the current working directory.

```bash
pwd
```

---

## ~

Represents the Home directory.

```bash
echo ~
```

---

## cd

Change directory.

```bash
cd folder_name
```

Useful shortcuts

```bash
cd ..
cd ~
```

---

# Listing Files

## ls

List directory contents.

```bash
ls
```

Useful options

```bash
ls .
ls ~
ls -l
ls -a
ls -la
ls -R
```

---

# Creating Files & Directories

## touch

Create an empty file.

```bash
touch file.txt
```

---

## mkdir

Create a directory.

```bash
mkdir folder
```

Nested directories

```bash
mkdir -p parent/child
```

---

# Writing into Files

Overwrite file

```bash
echo "Hello" > file.txt
```

Append text

```bash
echo "World" >> file.txt
```

---

# Copy Files

```bash
cp source destination
```

Copy directories

```bash
cp -r folder1 folder2
```

---

# Move/Rename Files

```bash
mv old.txt new.txt
```

---

# Delete Files

```bash
rm file.txt
```

Interactive delete

```bash
rm -i file.txt
```

Delete directory recursively

```bash
rm -r folder
```

Force delete

```bash
rm -rf folder
```

Remove empty directory

```bash
rmdir folder
```

---

# Viewing File Contents

## cat

View complete file.

```bash
cat file.txt
```

Line numbers

```bash
cat -n file.txt
```

---

## head

First 10 lines.

```bash
head file.txt
```

Specify lines

```bash
head -n 5 file.txt
```

Bytes

```bash
head -c 20 file.txt
```

---

## tail

Last 10 lines.

```bash
tail file.txt
```

Specify lines

```bash
tail -n 5 file.txt
```

Bytes

```bash
tail -c 20 file.txt
```

---

# Comparing Files

Compare two files

```bash
diff file1 file2
```

Compare directories

```bash
diff -r folder1 folder2
```

---

# Permissions

View permissions

```bash
ls -l
```

Change permissions

```bash
chmod 700 file.txt
chmod -R 755 folder
chmod u+x script.sh
chmod 600 secrets.txt
chmod 750 project
chmod 2770 shared_folder
```

Execute script

```bash
./script.sh
```

---

# Ownership

Change owner

```bash
sudo chown root:root file.txt
```

Recursive ownership

```bash
sudo chown -R root:root folder
```

Example

```bash
sudo chown -R dev_lead:developers project
```

---

# User Management

Create user

```bash
sudo useradd username
```

Create with home directory

```bash
sudo useradd -m username
```

View user

```bash
grep username /etc/passwd
```

Set password

```bash
sudo passwd username
```

Lock account

```bash
sudo passwd -l username
```

Unlock account

```bash
sudo passwd -u username
```

Delete user

```bash
sudo userdel -r username
```

Change home directory

```bash
sudo usermod -d /home/newhome username
```

Change shell

```bash
sudo usermod -s /bin/bash username
```

Add to sudo group

```bash
sudo usermod -aG sudo username
```

Check groups

```bash
groups username
```

Switch user

```bash
su - username
```

Encrypted passwords

```bash
sudo cat /etc/shadow
```

---

# Log Investigation

Search text

```bash
grep ERROR app.log
```

Exact word

```bash
grep -w ERROR app.log
```

Case insensitive

```bash
grep -i error app.log
```

Multiple patterns

```bash
grep -iE 'fail|error'
```

Redirect output

```bash
grep ERROR app.log > report.txt
```

Append output

```bash
grep worker nginx.conf >> report.txt
```

---

# Kernel Logs

```bash
sudo dmesg
```

Search boot errors

```bash
sudo dmesg | grep -iE 'fail|error'
```

---

# Useful Symbols

| Symbol | Meaning |
|---------|----------|
| `>` | Overwrite file |
| `>>` | Append to file |
| `|` | Pipe output |
| `~` | Home directory |
| `.` | Current directory |
| `..` | Parent directory |
| `-R` | Recursive |
| `-r` | Recursive (depends on command) |
| `-a` | Show hidden files |
| `-l` | Long listing |
| `-h` | Human readable |

